title: Alien breakthrough: NASA makes MASSIVE leap in hunt for extraterrestrial life
text:
NASA BREAKTHROUGH: NASA has made a shock discovery on Enceladus 
Ocean world Enceladus would appear to be one of the many cold, icy and inhabitable landmarks in the solar system. 
But Saturn's moon has been earmarked as a potential home for other life after a salt water ocean was found beneath the moon's crust. 
And experts believe there could be hydrothermal activity as well, which would further support alien life. 13 signs of alien life Tuesday, 15th November 2016 Daily Star Pictures brings you 13 mind-blowing signs that aliens exist. 1 / 13 Shutterstock / Leo Blanchette More than 40,000 Americans have taken out insurance against being abducted by aliens. “That has altered the way we think about where life might be found in our own Solar System, and in the worlds beyond” Linda Spilker 
NASA's Cassini spacecraft has now detected geysers under the planet's surface erupting into space. 
The plumes emitted from the planet included gases and salts as well as water vapour, proving the existence of the global saltwater ocean. 
Cassini project scientist Linda Spilker said extensive study of the moon has suggested it is being heated by tidal forces from Saturn, and could well support organic life. 
GETTY ALRIGHT GEYSER: How the water supply might look 
Life has been found in similar conditions in extinct oceans under the surface of the earth. 
She added: "That has altered the way we think about where life might be found in our own Solar System, and in the worlds beyond." 2016: Amazing pictures taken from a year in space Wednesday, 21st December 2016 2016 was a year full of new stunning imagery taken from Space 1 / 15 NASA Aug. 19, 2016: Expedition 48 Commander Jeff Williams (shown here) and Flight Engineer Kate Rubins of NASA successfully installed the first of two international docking adapters during a five hour and 58-minute spacewalk 
Other ocean worlds such as Jupiter's moon Europa , Saturn's moon Titan and Neptune's moon Triton are also being studied for alien life forms.
